projects/ecommerce-microservices-platform/apps/web-store/verify-webstore-*.mjs
projects/ecommerce-microservices-platform/apps/web-store/webstore-*.png

# HotSpot crash artifacts (TASK-MONO-354). Four of these — 1.06 MB of a JVM that ran
# out of memory — rode into `e839bb26b init wms-platform` and sat in
# libs/java-observability/ ever since, referenced by nothing. They are a recurring
# hazard rather than a one-off: a JVM OOM on a dev machine scatters them wherever the
# process happened to be running, so deleting them without an ignore rule just means
# the next crash re-commits them. Named exactly (not `*.log`) so a deliberately
# committed log fixture is never swallowed.
hs_err_pid*.log
replay_pid*.log

# --- infra/demo/aws (TASK-MONO-366) -----------------------------------------
# Terraform state carries resource IDs and can carry secrets; tfvars carries the
# operator's own public IP (admin_ssh_cidr). Neither belongs in a public repo.
# `terraform.tfvars.example` IS committed — it is the reproduction contract.
infra/demo/aws/terraform/terraform.tfvars
infra/demo/aws/terraform/*.tfstate
infra/demo/aws/terraform/*.tfstate.*
infra/demo/aws/terraform/.terraform/
infra/demo/aws/terraform/.terraform.lock.hcl
# 저장된 plan 은 tfvars 값(공인 IP CIDR)을 그대로 품는다. 이름 하나만 막으면
# `-out=tfplan.bin` 같은 변형이 그대로 새어 나간다 — 실제로 새어 나갈 뻔했다(MONO-389).
infra/demo/aws/terraform/tfplan*
infra/demo/aws/terraform/*.tfplan
infra/demo/aws/terraform/lambda/__pycache__/
infra/demo/aws/terraform/*.zip
